      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Easter ¶ 1883. ¶  ¶ Though I am not a member of the Phylloxera-Commission, dear Mr Dyer, I have once officially and once privately travelled over the vineries, devastated by that insect-pest. The evid...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">83.03.25b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Thiselton-Dyer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1882-90, ff. 61-2.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Easter</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">1883.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Though I am not a member of the Phylloxera-Commission, dear Mr Dyer, I have once officially and once privately travelled over the vineries, devastated by that insect-pest. The evidence is so conclusive and the identification so complete, that I never troubled, to preserve specimens; but to remove scepticism of the entomologic Society, I will bring some of the "corpus delicti" when next I travel beyond Geelong, as I shall likely find yet the ova and unwinged insect on remnants of roots. Kindly let your friends remember, that we have in Australia now-a-days also splendid microscopes, and that we also here fairly know, how to use them.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>An Entomological Society report was sceptical about the presence of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Phylloxera</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in Victoria: see M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 21 December 1882 and notes thereto.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I got some new Macrozamia Material from N.S.W. lately, or rather additional Material, which I will examine for improvement of diagnosis; but though the specimens are from various distant localities no actual novelty seems to be among them.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Should your Ottelia ovalifolia have suddenly perished,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J. Hooker, 29 June 1882 (in this edition as 82-06-29b) and notes thereto.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I will try to get more seeds; but we have the plant not near Melbourne. Aquatics often go suddenly off in culture, because — as my long horticultural experience has taught me, — they did not get a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">sufficiency of nutritive soil</hi>
               </seg>, to sustain the rapid growth.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I continue posted up on the American Vines Experiments through Planchons "La Vigne Americaine",<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See Planchon (1875), pp. 112-16.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and gave more particularly the best varieties already in the German Translation of the "Select plants".<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B83.13.06, pp. 419-25; for Planchon citations, see discussion under<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Vitus riparia</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">V. vinifera</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">. See also entries on these species in subsequent editions for additional notes.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Of course, no sane person would think of introducing living specimens of any Vitis from N. America. I raised the two "Scuppernongs" &amp; others<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">from seeds</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>many years ago.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to T. Wilson, 16 June 1881.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your service of calling forth the Cinchona-plantations in Jamaica alone would have given you claims to the C.M.G., not to speak of your multifarious efforts otherwise, to aid in the development of the rural wealth of the Colonial Empire of Britain.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I look forward with great eagerness to the vol. of Monocotyledoneae of the Genera,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83).</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>which will be a crowning piece of a grand structure in science.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My "Census"<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B8</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">3.03.04.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was under private printing Contract, so as to be done in 1882. Hence I could not delay the issue, til the genera were completed. May I beg of you, to read the preface carefully, and to remember, that I recommended to the illustrious authors of the "genera", to incorporate the Monochlamydeae with the other group[s],<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">before the work was commenced</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>20 years ago!<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The preface to B8</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">3</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">0</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">3.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">04</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>contains an argument for the distribution of genera and the sequence of orders of plants that differs from that used in Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83). For M’s early comments on the unsatisfactory nature of Monochlamydeae as a group, see M to G. Bentham, 24 January 1862. See also Maroske (2006).</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Hence in adhering to my views, emphatically expressed, before I knew of the plan of the genera, I am free to steer my own course without the slightest wish to interfere with the "genera" by any innovation of recent date from here.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Kindly remember me to Mr Bentham, and Sir Joseph, and let me remain</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Cinchona</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Macrozamia</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Monochlamydeae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Monocotyledoneae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ottelia ovalifolia</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Vitis</p>
         </div>
      </body>
